Ã¡Â»â€˜i vÃ¡Â»â€ºi khu vÃ¡Â»Â±c v&ugrave;ng biÃ¡Â»Æ’n Ã„ï¿½&ocirc;ng BÃ¡ÂºÂ¯c ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam n&oacute;i ri&ecirc;ng v&agrave; miÃ¡Â»ï¿½n BÃ¡ÂºÂ¯c ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam n&oacute;i chung.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cb60a1bf5b_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Ã„ï¿½Ã¡Â»â„¢ng Thien Cung </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><br />TÃ¡Â»Â« hÃ†Â¡n 500 nÃ„Æ’m vÃ¡Â»ï¿½ trÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»â€ºc trong b&agrave;i thÃ†Â¡ LÃ¡Â»â„¢ nhÃ¡ÂºÂ­p V&acirc;n Ã„ï¿½Ã¡Â»â€œn, NguyÃ¡Â»â€¦n Tr&atilde;i Ã„â€˜&atilde; lÃ¡ÂºÂ§n Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ§u ti&ecirc;n ca ngÃ¡Â»Â£i vÃ¡Â»â€¹nh HÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ Long l&agrave; \"kÃ¡Â»Â³ quan Ã„â€˜&aacute; dÃ¡Â»Â±ng giÃ¡Â»Â¯a trÃ¡Â»ï¿½i cao\". NÃ„Æ’m 1962 BÃ¡Â»â„¢ VÃ„Æ’n h&oacute;a-Th&ocirc;ng tin ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam Ã„â€˜&atilde; xÃ¡ÂºÂ¿p hÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ng vÃ¡Â»â€¹nh HÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ Long l&agrave; di t&iacute;ch danh thÃ¡ÂºÂ¯ng cÃ¡ÂºÂ¥p quÃ¡Â»â€˜c gia Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»â€œng thÃ¡Â»ï¿½i quy hoÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ch v&ugrave;ng bÃ¡ÂºÂ£o vÃ¡Â»â€¡. NÃ„Æ’m 1994 v&ugrave;ng l&otilde;i cÃ¡Â»Â§a vÃ¡Â»â€¹nh HÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ Long Ã„â€˜Ã†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£c UNESCO c&ocirc;ng nhÃ¡ÂºÂ­n l&agrave; Di sÃ¡ÂºÂ£n Thi&ecirc;n nhi&ecirc;n ThÃ¡ÂºÂ¿ giÃ¡Â»â€ºi vÃ¡Â»â€ºi gi&aacute; trÃ¡Â»â€¹ thÃ¡ÂºÂ©m mÃ¡Â»Â¹ (ti&ecirc;u chuÃ¡ÂºÂ©n vii), v&agrave; Ã„â€˜Ã†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£c t&aacute;i c&ocirc;ng nhÃ¡ÂºÂ­n lÃ¡ÂºÂ§n thÃ¡Â»Â© 2 vÃ¡Â»â€ºi gi&aacute; trÃ¡Â»â€¹ ngoÃ¡ÂºÂ¡i hÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ng to&agrave;n cÃ¡ÂºÂ§u vÃ¡Â»ï¿½ Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»â€¹a chÃ¡ÂºÂ¥t-Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»â€¹a mÃ¡ÂºÂ¡o (ti&ecirc;u chuÃ¡ÂºÂ©n viii) v&agrave;o nÃ„Æ’m 2000. C&ugrave;ng vÃ¡Â»â€ºi vÃ¡Â»â€¹nh Nha Trang cÃ¡Â»Â§a ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam, vÃ¡Â»â€¹nh HÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ Long l&agrave; mÃ¡Â»â„¢t trong sÃ¡Â»â€˜ 29 vÃ¡Â»â€¹nh Ã„â€˜Ã†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£c C&acirc;u lÃ¡ÂºÂ¡c bÃ¡Â»â„¢ nhÃ¡Â»Â¯ng vÃ¡Â»â€¹nh Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¹p nhÃ¡ÂºÂ¥t thÃ¡ÂºÂ¿ giÃ¡Â»â€ºi xÃ¡ÂºÂ¿p hÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ng v&agrave; ch&iacute;nh thÃ¡Â»Â©c c&ocirc;ng nhÃ¡ÂºÂ­n v&agrave;o th&aacute;ng 7 nÃ„Æ’m 2003.<br /><br />VÃ¡Â»â€¹nh HÃ¡ÂºÂ¡ Long c&ugrave;ng vÃ¡Â»â€ºi Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ£o C&aacute;t B&agrave; tÃ¡ÂºÂ¡o th&agrave;nh 1 trong 21 khu du lÃ¡Â»â€¹ch quÃ¡Â»â€˜c gia ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam</p>','Wikipedia','','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cb69b56214_square.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cb69b56214_thumbnail.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cb69b56214_small.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cb69b56214_crop.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cb69b56214_medium.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cb69b56214_large.jpg','active',1,'2010-08-31 15:06:36',1,'admin','2010-08-31 15:39:57',1,'admin',1,'admin','2010-08-31 15:07:11',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'vi_VN'),(17,1,'Nha Trang','','nha-trang','<p>Nha Trang About this sound pronunciation is a coastal city and capital of Kh&aacute;nh H&ograve;a province, on the South Central Coast of Vietnam.</p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is bounded on the North by Ninh Ho&agrave; district, on the East by the South China Sea, on the South by Cam Ranh town and on the West by Di&ecirc;n Kh&aacute;nh district. The city has about 300,000 inhabitants, a number which is projected to increase to between 500,000 and 600,000 inhabitants by 2020 according to an estimation of Nha Trang Administrative Board Statistics.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cba2d1b84a_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Nha Trang&acute;s coastline</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nha Trang is well known for its pristine beaches and excellent scuba diving and is fast becoming a popular destination for international tourists, attracting large numbers of backpackers as well as more affluent travelers on the Southeast Asia circuit. It is already very popular with Vietnamese tourists. Nha Trang Bay is widely considered as amongst the world\'s most beautiful bays. Tourists are welcome to participate in the Sea Festival, held biennially. Nha Trang was the site of the Miss Universe 2008 Pageant on July 14, 2008 and it will also host Miss Earth 2010.<br /><br />Historically, the city was known as Kauthara under the Champa. The city is still home to the famous Po Nagar Tower built by the Champa. Being a coastal city, Nha Trang is a center for marine science based at the Nha Trang Oceanography Institute. The Hon Mun marine protected area is one of four first marine protected areas in the world admitted by the IUCN.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cba2c0dd5e_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Nha Trang\'s beach</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Commercial flights to Nha Trang no longer use the city\'s municipal airport, but fly to the larger Cam Ranh International Airport, a former U.S. Air Force Base (built during the Vietnam War) located approximately 35 km south of Nha Trang (see the Transport section below for additional details).<br /><br />The French-Swiss bacteriologist Alexandre Yersin (who discovered the Yersinia pestis bacterium) identified himself with Nha Trang\'s life for 50 years (affectionately known as &Ocirc;ng NÃ„Æ’m). He established the Indochina Pasteur Institute (now known as the Nha Trang Pasteur Institute) devoted to research on the bubonic plague. Yersin died in Nha Trang on March 1, 1943. A street in the city is named after him, there is a shrine located next to his tomb, and his house has been converted into the Yersin Museum.</p>','Wikipedia','','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbae63edcd_square.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbae63edcd_thumbnail.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbae63edcd_small.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbae63edcd_crop.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbae63edcd_medium.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbae63edcd_large.jpg','active',3,'2010-08-31 15:18:51',1,'admin','2010-08-31 15:43:45',1,'admin',1,'admin','2010-08-31 15:18:57',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'en_US'),(18,3,'TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t Holiday','','tet-holiday','<p>TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t Nguy&ecirc;n Ã„ï¿½&aacute;n, more commonly known by its shortened name TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t, is the most important and popular holiday and festival in Vietnam.</p>','<p>TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t is celebrated on the same day as Chinese New Year though exceptions arise due to the one-hour time difference between Hanoi and Beijing. It takes place from the first day of the first month of the Lunar calendar (around late January or early February) until at least the third day. Many Vietnamese prepare for TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t by cooking special holiday foods and cleaning the house. There are a lot of customs practiced during TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t, like visiting a person\'s house on the first day of the new year (x&ocirc;ng nh&agrave;), ancestral worshipping, wishing New Year\'s greetings, giving lucky money to children and elderly people, and opening a shop.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbaa183723_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t display in Saigon</em></p>\r\n<p>TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t is also an occasion for pilgrims and family reunions. During TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t, Vietnamese visit their relatives and temples, forgetting about the troubles of the past year and hoping for a better upcoming year. They consider TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t to be the first day of spring and the festival is often called HÃ¡Â»â„¢i xu&acirc;n (spring festival).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbaa08d743_medium.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Hoa mai</em></p>\r\n<p>Vietnamese people usually return to their families during TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t. Some return to worship at the family altar or visit the graves of their ancestors in their homeland. Although TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t is a national holiday among all Vietnamese, each region and religion has its own customs.</p>\r\n<p>TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t in the three Vietnamese regions can be divided into three periods, known as TÃ¡ÂºÂ¥t Ni&ecirc;n (Before New Year\'s Eve), Giao ThÃ¡Â»Â«a (New Year\'s Eve), and T&acirc;n Ni&ecirc;n (the New Year), representing the preparation before TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t, the eve of TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t, and the days of and following TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t, respectively.</p>','Wikipedia','','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbaa3b26b3_square.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbaa3b26b3_thumbnail.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbaa3b26b3_small.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbaa3b26b3_crop.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbaa3b26b3_medium.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbaa3b26b3_large.jpg','active',3,'2010-08-31 15:20:20',1,'admin',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'admin','2010-08-31 15:20:27',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'en_US'),(19,13,'Nha Trang','','nha-trang','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nha Trang l&agrave; mÃ¡Â»â„¢t th&agrave;nh phÃ¡Â»â€˜ ven biÃ¡Â»Æ’n v&agrave; l&agrave; trung t&acirc;m ch&iacute;nh trÃ¡Â»â€¹, kinh tÃ¡ÂºÂ¿, vÃ„Æ’n h&oacute;a, khoa hÃ¡Â»ï¿½c kÃ¡Â»Â¹ thuÃ¡ÂºÂ­t v&agrave; du lÃ¡Â»â€¹ch cÃ¡Â»Â§a tÃ¡Â»â€°nh Kh&aacute;nh H&ograve;a, ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam.</p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">TrÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»â€ºc khi trÃ¡Â»Å¸ th&agrave;nh phÃ¡ÂºÂ§n Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¥t cÃ¡Â»Â§a ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam, Nha Trang thuÃ¡Â»â„¢c vÃ¡Â»ï¿½ Chi&ecirc;m Th&agrave;nh. C&aacute;c di t&iacute;ch cÃ¡Â»Â§a ngÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»ï¿½i ChÃ„Æ’m vÃ¡ÂºÂ«n c&ograve;n tÃ¡ÂºÂ¡i nhiÃ¡Â»ï¿½u nÃ†Â¡i Ã¡Â»Å¸ Nha Trang. Nha Trang Ã„â€˜Ã†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£c ThÃ¡Â»Â§ tÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»â€ºng ch&iacute;nh phÃ¡Â»Â§ ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam c&ocirc;ng nhÃ¡ÂºÂ­n l&agrave; Ã„â€˜&ocirc; thÃ¡Â»â€¹ loÃ¡ÂºÂ¡i 1 v&agrave;o ng&agrave;y 22 th&aacute;ng 4 nÃ„Æ’m 2009. Ã„ï¿½&acirc;y l&agrave; mÃ¡Â»â„¢t trong 6 Ã„â€˜&ocirc; thÃ¡Â»â€¹ loÃ¡ÂºÂ¡i 1 trÃ¡Â»Â±c thuÃ¡Â»â„¢c tÃ¡Â»â€°nh cÃ¡Â»Â§a ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam<br /><br />C&aacute;c b&atilde;i biÃ¡Â»Æ’n Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¹p cÃ¡Â»Â§a th&agrave;nh phÃ¡Â»â€˜ n&agrave;y Ã„â€˜&atilde; biÃ¡ÂºÂ¿n n&oacute; th&agrave;nh mÃ¡Â»â„¢t danh lam thÃ¡ÂºÂ¯ng cÃ¡ÂºÂ£nh. NÃ†Â¡i Ã„â€˜&acirc;y cÃ…Â©ng Ã„â€˜Ã†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£c biÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ¿n nhÃ†Â° mÃ¡Â»â„¢t Ã„â€˜Ã