 Immediately, his horse whinny resoundingly. He stopped and gone to the highest mountain- NghÃ„Â©a LÃ„Â©nh, saw four directions. At last, he decided to choose this place.<br /><br />Ph&uacute; ThÃ¡Â»ï¿½ is fat and green midland area. In Fengshui opinion, Phong Ch&acirc;u is the land of \"sÃ†Â¡n chÃ¡ÂºÂ§u thÃ¡Â»Â§y tÃ¡Â»Â¥\" (place where mountains and rivers gather), \"long chÃ¡ÂºÂ§u hÃ¡Â»â€¢ phÃ¡Â»Â¥c\" (place where dragons and tigers attend upon), \"phÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£ng bay ngÃ¡Â»Â±a chÃ¡ÂºÂ¡y\" (place where phoenixes fly and horses run) and the land where\'s abundant in \"kh&iacute; thi&ecirc;ng s&ocirc;ng n&uacute;i\" (sacred country\'s qi- flow of energy). This place is full of obstacles and difficult of access that\'s easy to protect, but also easy of access to welcome people come from other places. This is the confluence of 3 rivers: Ã„ï¿½&agrave; river, red water- Thao river and clear blue water- L&ocirc; river. In front of NghÃ„Â©a LÃ„Â©nh mountain, it\'s ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Tr&igrave; three- way crossroads where there\'re tens of turtle- shape low hill direct to H&ugrave;ng temple. Behind NghÃ„Â©a LÃ„Â©nh mountain, it\'s Hy CÃ†Â°Ã†Â¡ng village form a letter- bringing phoenix shape. At the right of this mountain, there\'s Khang PhÃ¡Â»Â¥ hill like an attending tiger. At the left of this mountain, there\'s An Th&aacute;i hill like an arrow- shooting army general for protecting this temple. At the foot of the mountain, there\'s CÃ¡Â»â€¢ T&iacute;ch village on the horse- shape hill and ThÃ¡ÂºÂ­m Th&igrave;nh village where villagers stay awake throung a night to pound rice in order that Lang Li&ecirc;u make b&aacute;nh chÃ†Â°ng and b&aacute;nh d&agrave;y. From ThÃ¡ÂºÂ­m Th&igrave;nh to Ph&uacute; LÃ¡Â»â„¢c, there\'re hills which\'re incarnation of 100 elephants of which 99 elephants direct to H&ugrave;ng temple but 1 elephant didn\'t. That\'s why the God cut off its head and the hill of this elephant still overflow blood nowadays. NghÃ„Â©a LÃ„Â©nh mountain- 175m high like head of a dragon direct to the South and the body of this dragon are TrÃ¡Â»ï¿½c mountain, VÃ¡ÂºÂ·n mountain and Pheo mountain. NghÃ„Â©a LÃ„Â©nh mountain, VÃ¡ÂºÂ·n mountain and TrÃ¡Â»ï¿½c mountain\'s regarded as \"Tam SÃ†Â¡n CÃ¡ÂºÂ¥m Ã„ï¿½Ã¡Â»â€¹a\" (3 forbidden mountain).</p>','Wikipedia','','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_square.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_thumbnail.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_small.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_crop.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_medium.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccb95d5d73_large.jpg','active',3,'2010-08-31 16:27:03',1,'admin','2010-08-31 16:30:03',1,'admin',1,'admin','2010-08-31 16:27:10',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'en_US'),(28,21,'LÃ¡Â»â€¦ hÃ¡Â»â„¢i Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»ï¿½n HÃƒÂ¹ng','','le-hoi-den-hung','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">H&ugrave;ng temple, locating in NghÃ„Â©a LÃ„Â©nh mountain, CÃ¡Â»â€¢ T&iacute;ch village, Hy CÃ†Â°Ã†Â¡ng commune, Phong Ch&acirc;u district, Ph&uacute; ThÃ¡Â»ï¿½ province, is the most sacred Vietnamese national historic and cultural complex site.</p>','<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D&ugrave; ai Ã„â€˜i ngÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£c vÃ¡Â»ï¿½ xu&ocirc;i<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; NhÃ¡Â»â€º ng&agrave;y giÃ¡Â»â€” tÃ¡Â»â€¢ m&ugrave;ng mÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»ï¿½i th&aacute;ng ba<br /><br />LÃ¡Â»â€¦ hÃ¡Â»â„¢i Ã„â€˜Ã¡Â»ï¿½n H&ugrave;ng c&ograve;n gÃ¡Â»ï¿½i l&agrave; GiÃ¡Â»â€” tÃ¡Â»â€¢ H&ugrave;ng VÃ†Â°Ã†Â¡ng l&agrave; mÃ¡Â»â„¢t lÃ¡Â»â€¦ hÃ¡Â»â„¢i lÃ¡Â»â€ºn mang tÃ¡ÂºÂ§m v&oacute;c quÃ¡Â»â€˜c gia Ã¡Â»Å¸ ViÃ¡Â»â€¡t Nam, tÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»Å¸ng nhÃ¡Â»â€º v&agrave; tÃ¡Â»ï¿½ l&ograve;ng biÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t Ã†Â¡n c&ocirc;ng lao lÃ¡ÂºÂ­p nÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»â€ºc cÃ¡Â»Â§a c&aacute;c vua H&ugrave;ng, nhÃ¡Â»Â¯ng vÃ¡Â»â€¹ vua Ã„â€˜Ã¡ÂºÂ§u ti&ecirc;n cÃ¡Â»Â§a d&acirc;n tÃ¡Â»â„¢c. LÃ¡Â»â€¦ hÃ¡Â»â„¢i diÃ¡Â»â€¦n ra v&agrave;o ng&agrave;y 10 th&aacute;ng 3 &acirc;m lÃ¡Â»â€¹ch, tuy nhi&ecirc;n, lÃ¡Â»â€¦ hÃ¡Â»â„¢i thÃ¡Â»Â±c chÃ¡ÂºÂ¥t Ã„â€˜&atilde; diÃ¡Â»â€