o tÃ¡Â»â€ºi hÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t buÃ¡Â»â€¢i s&aacute;ng khai mÃ¡ÂºÂ¡c.</p>','Wikipedia','','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_square.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_thumbnail.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_small.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_crop.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_medium.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2f967c8c_large.jpg','active',2,'2010-08-31 16:42:26',1,'admin','2010-08-31 17:01:33',1,'admin',1,'admin','2010-08-31 16:42:49',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'vi_VN'),(30,3,'Hoa Lu ancient capital festival','','hoa-lu-ancient-capital-festival','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hoa Lu ancient capital Festival opened in the spring.</p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Start a ceremony at the Yellow River Long procession of the temple 2 Kings. Group stage near the procession of King Dinh Tien Hoang Temple. There will be many games in the Assembly. Hoa Lu Festival described the history of Vietnam from 968 to 1010 with many changes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7ccee363d4b_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Hoa Lu ancient capital Festival&nbsp; </em></p>','Wikipedia','','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_square.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_thumbnail.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_small.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_crop.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_medium.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd2542ef64_large.jpg','active',2,'2010-08-31 17:00:21',1,'admin',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'admin','2010-08-31 17:00:29',0,0,0,0,NULL,0,'en_US'),(31,3,'Lantern Festival','','lantern-festival','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Lantern Festival or \"TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t ThÃ†Â°Ã¡Â»Â£ng Nguy&ecirc;n\" or \"TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t Nguy&ecirc;n Ti&ecirc;u\"(Vietnamese: TÃ¡ÂºÂ¿t Nguy&ecirc;n ti&ecirc;u) in Vietnam; is a festival celebrated on the fifteenth day of the first month in the lunar year in the Chinese calendar, the last day of the Lunar Chinese New Year celebration.</p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is not to be confused with the Mid-Autumn Festival, which is sometimes also known as the \"Lantern Festival\" in locations such as Singapore and Malaysia. During the Lantern Festival, children go out at night to temples carrying paper lanterns and solve riddles on the lanterns. It officially ends the Chinese New Year celebrations.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_crop.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Lantern Festival celebration in Shijiazhuang.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In ancient times, the lanterns were fairly simple, for only the emperor and noblemen had large ornate ones; in modern times, lanterns have been embellished with many complex designs. For example, lanterns are now often made in shapes of animals.<br /><br />The Lantern Festival is also known as the Little New Year since it marks the end of the series of celebrations starting from the Chinese New Year.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59084397_crop.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Year 2008 Taiwan Lantern Festival in Tainan, Taiwan.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In some region and countries, this festival is also regarded as the Chinese version of St. Valentine\'s Day, a day celebrating love and affection between lovers in Chinese tradition and culture.</p>','Wikipedia','','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_square.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_thumbnail.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_small.jpg','/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cd59188688_crop.jpg','/uplo